title OG Image Generation Flow

|Script (generate-og-image.js)|
start

:Invoke **generateOgImage()**\nvia `bun run og-image`;

fork
  :Call **getCommandCount()**;

  |File System|
  :Open `source/skills/` directory\n(skillsDir);

  if (skillsDir exists?) then (no)
    :Return 0;
  else (yes)
    :Iterate over entries\nin skillsDir;
    repeat
      if (entry.isDirectory()?) then (no)
        :Skip entry;
      else (yes)
        if (SKILL.md exists\nin entry dir?) then (no)
          :Skip entry;
        else (yes)
          :Read SKILL.md content\n(UTF-8);
          if (Frontmatter\nblock found?) then (no)
            :Skip entry;
          else (yes)
            if (user-invocable: true\nAND not DEPRECATED?) then (yes)
              :Increment count;
            else (no)
              :Skip entry;
            endif
          endif
        endif
      endif
    repeat while (more entries?) is (yes)
    -> no;
    :Return **commands** count\n(integer);
  endif

fork again
  |Script (generate-og-image.js)|
  :Call **getExtensionDataUrl()**;

  |File System|
  :Read `public/assets/\nextension-detection.png`\nas binary buffer;
  :Encode buffer to\nBase64 string;
  :Return **extensionDataUrl**\n`data:image/png;base64,...`;

end fork

|Script (generate-og-image.js)|
:Log detected command count;
:Build self-contained **HTML string**\n— inject `commands` count\n— inject `extensionDataUrl` into <img src>\n— link Google Fonts CDN\n  (Cormorant Garamond, Instrument Sans,\n   Space Grotesk)\n— viewport 1200×630 px;

|Playwright (Chromium)|
:Launch **headless Chromium**\n`chromium.launch()`;
:Create new **page**\n`viewport: { width: 1200, height: 630 }`\n`deviceScaleFactor: 1`;
:Set page content\n`page.setContent(html,\n  { waitUntil: 'networkidle' })`\n— render HTML + fetch Google Fonts;
:Wait for all fonts to load\n`page.evaluate(\n  () => document.fonts.ready\n)`;
:Capture **JPEG screenshot**\n`page.screenshot({\n  path: OUTPUT_PATH,\n  type: 'jpeg',\n  quality: 90\n})`;
:Close browser\n`browser.close()`;

|File System|
:Read output file stats\n`fs.statSync(OUTPUT_PATH)`;
:Return file size in bytes;

|Script (generate-og-image.js)|
:Log output path\nand file size (KB);

stop

|Script (generate-og-image.js)|
floating note left
  **On any unhandled error:**
  console.error(err)
  process.exit(1)
end note

@enduml
